# --- Harness runtime artifacts -------------------------------------------------
# State files are committed (they ARE the memory), but transient run output is not.
# NOTE: git does NOT support inline (trailing) comments — keep comments on their own lines.
# per-loop logs, transcripts, ledger, scratch:
harness/.runs/
# live token/cost accounting for the current run:
harness/.budget.json
# current loop checkpoint ref (crash-recovery breadcrumb):
harness/.checkpoint
# fleet worker worktrees (parallel builds; parked ones are cleaned up by hand):
harness/.worktrees/
# plugin/engine is the runtime engine source (this dev repo dogfoods it post-E2 flip); never track
# runtime artifacts that a direct-engine run may write there:
plugin/engine/.runs/
plugin/engine/.budget.json
plugin/engine/.checkpoint
plugin/engine/.worktrees/
# fleet workers' escalation channel (surfaced into state/handoff.md by the runner):
FLEET_NOTES.md
*.harness.log
# regenerated each context reset; not worth versioning:
state/handoff.md
# personal overrides (permissions, env) — never commit:
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- Secrets -------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.cer
secrets/
**/credentials.json
**/id_rsa
**/id_ed25519
.npmrc
.pgpass
.aws/credentials
**/*.keystore

# --- OS / editor ---------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.swp

# --- Add your stack's build/dep artifacts below (or let /harness-init do it) ----
# node_modules/  dist/  build/  __pycache__/  .venv/  target/  bin/  obj/

# agent-internal memory (subagent scratch — never commit)
.claude/agent-memory/
.claude/worktrees/
